<%- include('partials/page-top') %>
<section class="tool-hero">
  <div>
    <p class="eyebrow">Data automation utility</p>
    <h1>Excel to JSON converter for APIs, imports, and automation.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Upload your Excel workbook, preview clean JSON immediately, and download the serialized file for APIs, low-code workflows,
      or analytics stacks. No tracking pixels or surprise storage — just a straightforward conversion pipeline you can trust.
    </p>
    <ul class="trust-points">
      <li>Supports .xls and .xlsx uploads up to 5 MB</li>
      <li>Preserves sheet-by-sheet structure with null-safe values</li>
      <li>Download a ready-to-use JSON file or copy the text payload</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="converter-card">
    <form action="/excel-to-json" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
      <label for="excelFile">Choose an Excel file</label>
      <input id="excelFile" name="excelFile" type="file" accept=".xls,.xlsx" required />
      <p class="help-text">We never persist uploads. Files stay in memory for conversion only.</p>
      <button type="submit" class="button primary btn btn-primary btn-modern full-width">Convert to JSON</button>
    </form>
    <% if (error) { %>
      <div class="flash flash-error" role="alert"><%= error %></div>
    <% } %>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="result-panel">
  <div class="result-card">
    <h2>JSON preview</h2>
    <p class="help-text">Each worksheet is preserved as a JSON array keyed by its sheet name.</p>
    <% if (result) { %>
      <p class="success-text">Successfully parsed <%= result.sheetCount %> worksheet(s). Review or download below.</p>
      <textarea readonly class="code-block" rows="14"><%= result.jsonString %></textarea>
      <div class="download-row">
        <form action="/excel-to-json/download" method="POST">
          <input type="hidden" name="payload" value="<%= result.downloadPayload %>" />
          <input type="hidden" name="fileName" value="<%= result.fileName %>" />
          <button type="submit" class="button primary btn btn-primary btn-modern">Download JSON file</button>
        </form>
        <p class="help-text">Or select the text above and copy it directly into your API client.</p>
      </div>
    <% } else { %>
      <textarea readonly class="code-block" rows="14">{"SampleSheet":[{"column":"value"}]}</textarea>
      <p class="help-text">Upload a spreadsheet to replace this sample output with your data.</p>
    <% } %>
  </div>
  <div class="result-card">
    <h2>How the converter cleans your data</h2>
    <ul class="checklist">
      <li>Trims leading and trailing whitespace for predictable JSON keys.</li>
      <li>Sets empty cells to <code>null</code> so downstream systems can validate missing values.</li>
      <li>Processes every sheet independently, keeping multi-tab workbooks intact.</li>
      <li>Runs entirely in memory — nothing is saved to disk or transmitted elsewhere.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="help-text">
      Need more structure? Pair the JSON output with your favorite validation library or schema registry to enforce data
      contracts across imports.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="seo-content">
  <h2>Why teams ship data faster with Excel to JSON automation</h2>
  <p>
    Manual spreadsheet cleanup delays integrations, BI dashboards, and internal tooling. This converter bridges the gap between
    how teams collect information (Excel) and how modern platforms ingest it (JSON). Common use cases include migrating CRM
    exports into RESTful services, feeding customer success notes into product analytics, and bulk-loading catalog data into
    headless commerce stacks.
  </p>
  <p>
    Because the transformation runs on the server, you can integrate it behind authentication, layer in rate limits, or extend
    it with custom validation. Keep the default experience simple for SEO and discoverability while layering advanced rules for
    production customers.
  </p>
  <h3>Deployment-ready talking points for search engines and buyers</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Free Excel to JSON converter optimized for API pipelines and webhooks.</li>
    <li>Secure, session-backed foundation that fits subscription or ad-supported monetization.</li>
    <li>High-signal content and structured data markup to rank for spreadsheet-to-JSON workflows.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
  <dl class="faq">
    <dt>What happens to my file after upload?</dt>
    <dd>Your spreadsheet is processed in memory only for conversion. Nothing is written to disk or stored after the request.</dd>
    <dt>Does the converter keep multiple sheets?</dt>
    <dd>Yes. Each worksheet is turned into its own array in the JSON payload and keyed by sheet name.</dd>
    <dt>Can I automate this?</dt>
    <dd>
      Absolutely. The endpoint runs on Express, so you can protect it with authentication, rate limiting, or your preferred
      monetization strategy, then reuse the JSON output in any downstream service.
    </dd>
  </dl>
</section>
<%- include('partials/page-bottom') %>
